Posta Rangers pressed for a goal and it came in the 58th minute after Dwang' recieve a pass from the midfield then dribbled past Michael Kibwage and released a ferocious shot which went straight into the net.Joseph at Lopala almost equalised for Rangers at death, buthis powerful shot went inches from the cross bar as Sofapaka survived a late onslaught from their opponents to garner maximum points.  Posta Rangers coach Stanley Okumbi suffered his second consecutive loss since taking over the mantle two weeks ago as his side fell 2-1 to former Sofapaka Sunday in their Football Kenya Federation Premier League match at the Moi International Sports Centre, Kasarani. 

Titus Achesa put 'Batoto ba Mungu' ahead in the 20th minute, before Lawrence Juma scored his eighth goal of the season in the 38th minute to seal the maximum points for coach Ken Odhiambo's charges. 



