"We have played well and my defenders denied them late in the game. Our game plan was to beat them in the first half and it worked for us," said Odhiambo. 

His opposite number Stanley Okumbi bemoaned the missed opportunities, saying he is under no pressure despite losing twice. 

"We missed clear cut opportunities and I feel we should have won. My players continue improving and we have picked positives from this loss as we focus on getting back to winning ways," said Okumbi. He has dared all those interested in the presidency to step into the ring and sell their agenda without undermining anyone. Devolution minister says that for a country to prosper, a strong foundation like the BBI is necessary. Participant voices anger at "unacceptable corruption at a time when Libya is going through a major crisis".